<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11953&amp;p=141472#p141472"><![CDATA[
I did some work in this space recently. <br /><br />I wrote a tool which will extract Vs. system size ROM files from iNES format files. Along with it I ran through all the iNES ROMs in my collection which matched a spec which I thought might work on Vs hardware.<br /><br />The results are posted here: <a href="https://github.com/cyberkni/NESToVSRoms/wiki/Game-Compatibility-List" class="postlink">https://github.com/cyberkni/NESToVSRoms/wiki/Game-Compatibility-List</a><br /><br />Note that you'll need an RC2C05 variety PPU for the games to look normal. I was considering attempting to modify one of the games to work on alternative PPUs before I got distracted from this project.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6863">cyberkni</a> — Wed Feb 18, 2015 1:58 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
