Super Dodge Ball is MMC1, as is Vs. Dr. Mario. Unfortunately, the MDS-VS1 board only supports 64 KiB PRG/CHR, and Super Dodge Ball is 128/128, so there would be some rework there...<br /><br />Super Dodge Ball also stops reading from $4017 if you select a one-player game.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Fri Oct 24, 2014 5:19 pm</p><hr />
